<title>ARGENTINA: Argentina's Bansud reaches agreement on IFC credit.</title>
<headline>Argentina's Bansud reaches agreement on IFC credit.</headline>
<dateline>BUENOS AIRES 1997-02-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Argentina's Bansud bank said Monday it reached agreement with the International Finance Corp to draw $25 million in credits for small and medium-sized firms.</p>
<p>The loans to the firms can be as long as eight years with a grace period of up to two years with payments based 180-day LIBOR plus a fixed spread.</p>
<p>The maximum amount of each loan will be $5 million.</p>
<p>Bansud will evaluate the smaller firms' projects that need financing.</p>
<p>((--Axel Bugge, Buenos Aires Newsroom, 541 318-0668))</p>
